    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Problem description.</h3>\n<p>\u00a0Suyash is a great magician and always helps the poor with his magic power in his town. One day a poor kid arrives in his door with 'N' coins.The poor kid was afraid that he would not survive long with 'N' coin so he asks Suyash for help.\nSuyash casts a spell in that 'N' coins.Because of the spell every day each of the coin produces three times of its identicals.For example, suppose on Day-1 the kid has 'a' coins , on Day-2 the kid will have 'a+3a' coins and so on.\nThe kid wants to know how many coins it will have on the 'M'th day.Since the kid is poor in maths,he asks for your help.\n</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n\n<p>The first line contains 'T',the number of test cases.\nEach of the 'i'th test case will contain two values N and M ,seperated by spaces.\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>\u00a0Each of the test case will contain the resultant coin in 'M' th day.\nSince the resultant coin is very large,print the answer modulo 10<sup>9</sup>+7.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>5</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>4</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>M</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>5</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<b>Example case 1.</b>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2 \n1 2\n3 4\n<b>Output:</b>\n4\n192\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> In the following test case, in Day-1,it has 1 coin.\nIn Day-2, it has 1 + (1*3) =4 coins due to the spell</p>",
